## Missing Analyses & Improvement Recommendations

> [!IMPORTANT]
> These are analyses that are **currently absent** from NB0-NB6 but would strengthen the paper. They are ordered by priority.

### High Priority (Do Before Paper Writing)

| # | Analysis | Why It Matters | Where |
|---|----------|---------------|-------|
| 1 | **Binomial chance-level test** (Script 1 above) | Determines how many participants are genuinely engaged vs. random guessing. Foundational for all other claims. | NB1 |
| 2 | **Speed-accuracy correlation** (Script 2 above) | Directly addresses the "protester" question. If fast = random, we need exclusions. | NB1 |
| 3 | **Learning effect test** (Script 3 above) | Strongest potential novel finding. If AI creates lasting learning, it's a major contribution. | NB3 |
| 4 | **Multiple comparison correction** | NB4 runs 30 Big5×performance correlations without FDR/Bonferroni correction. The Extraversion findings (p=0.001, p=0.0001) will survive correction, but marginal findings (Neuroticism p=0.06) may not. Apply Benjamini-Hochberg FDR. | NB4 |
| 5 | **Inter-rater reliability preparation** | When radiologist annotations arrive: compute Fleiss' κ among the 5 surgeons, then Cohen's κ between radiologist consensus and original ground truth. This quantifies the label noise problem. | New NB7 |

### Medium Priority (Strengthen the Paper)

| # | Analysis | Why It Matters | Where |
|---|----------|---------------|-------|
| 6 | **Batch effect test** | You ran two classroom batches. A simple t-test between Batch 1 and Batch 2 accuracy would show whether the social/environmental conditions differed. | NB1 or NB4 |
| 7 | **Bootstrap CIs for key findings** | The AI boost (d=0.601) and Extraversion correlation (r=-0.422) are your headline numbers. Bootstrap 95% CIs would show their stability beyond parametric assumptions. | NB1, NB4 |
| 8 | **Per-image difficulty analysis** | Some images are harder than others. Computing per-image accuracy and difficulty distribution would help contextualize errors and relate to the label noise finding. | NB6 or new |

