## On AI Accuracy Discrepancy (70% vs 74% vs 78%)

> [!WARNING]
> The numbers in NB0 show "AI Overall Accuracy: 77.8%", but your context says the model was 74% and participants saw 70%. This discrepancy MUST be clarified in the paper.

The 77.8% is calculated from the **trial data** (i.e., the AI predictions on the specific 50 images participants saw). The 70% is the AI's accuracy on the full dataset (which is what DANNY also used). The 74% is the model's overall trained accuracy.

**For the paper, you need to report:**
- The model's overall accuracy on the training/validation set (74%)
- The model's accuracy on the specific 50-image subset used in the study (77.8%)
- That the heatmaps and confidence scores reflect the 74% model

This difference (70% → 78% on the subset) likely arises because the 50-image subset happens to contain images the model is better at. This is important context.
